defaultPerformance Managementdefault&#xa0;
default3.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultIn April 2010 Wiltshire Police introduced a balanced scorecard as a performance management tool.  The intention of this system was to ‘take the numbers’ away from senior managers.  The reason for 
defaultthis was to encourage a culture of looking forward and ‘making things better than they otherwise would have been.’
default&#xa0;
default3.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultThis replaced a system where force performance was measured thorough a small number of 
defaultyear to date 
defaultKey Performance Indicators (KPI).  The
defaultse KPI’s were set against targets which were, in general, binary comparison with previous years data.  In addition 
defaultiQuanta
default data with comparison to Wiltshire’s family of forces was used mostly to give context to areas where KPI’s had worsened.
default&#xa0;
default3.3
default&#xa0; 
defaultIt
default is critic
defaultal to understand how senior managers 
defaultincorrectly 
defaultuse recorded crime statistics to measure and improve performance.
default  Below 
defaultis an 
defaultexample I witnessed in Wiltshire Police.
default&#xa0;
default3.4
default&#xa0; 
defaultDuring
default 2011Violent crime, both volume and detection rates, were identified at an issue
default in our County division.  Pressure was brought to bear on the performance team to identify ‘how much of a 
defaultnumerical 
defaultreduction’ would be required for this to no longer be an issue.  The hierarchical nature of the police made it impossible to resist
default providin
defaultg 
defaultthis 
defaultinformation 
defaulteven though we felt it 
defaultc
defaultould 
defaultrisk
default dysfunctional behaviour.
default&#xa0;
default3.5
default&#xa0; 
defaultRather than focus on activities that would have a positive impact on future performance (e.g. improving the quality of investigations or focussed activity to target Night Time E
defaultconomy (NTE) violence) resource w
defaultas put into reviewing all Year t
defaulto Date undetected violent crime.  
default&#xa0;
default3.6
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe purpose was to identify administrative oversights, including incorrect crime classification, crimes not being recorded as detected or crimes that had b
defaulteen identified as being ‘no crime’ not having been recorded as such .  In my opinion this had little or no impact in reducing crime or improving service delivery to victims of crime.  This activity, I believe, was undertaken full-time by two members of sta
defaultff for at least a month.
default&#xa0;
default3.7
default&#xa0; 
defaultReviewing previously completed crimes was a tactic often employed by managers in Wiltshire Police during my tenure within the force performance team.
default  I suspect Wiltshire Police are not unique in utilising this tactic.
default   
default&#xa0;
default4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMisuedefault odefaultf defaultiQuantadefault Ddefaultata.default&#xa0;default4.1
